-- 09-negotiation-consensus.cell
-- N perspective cells argue positions. A mediator finds common ground and
-- remaining disagreements. Perspectives revise. Mediator re-evaluates.
-- вҠўвҲҳ loop until supermajority consensus.
--
-- Tests: N-way parallel evaluation, вҠўвҠў spawner, judgment-gated вҠўвҲҳ iteration,
--        В§ quotation for perspective rewriting
--
-- Question: "What programming language should a startup use for their backend?"
-- Perspectives: CTO (pragmatist), Senior Dev (perfectionist),
--               Junior Dev (learner), Investor (cost-conscious)

вҠў question
  given text вүЎ "What programming language should a startup use for their backend?"
  yield text

  вҠЁ text is a debatable question with multiple valid positions

вҠў perspective-cto
  given questionвҶ’text
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are a pragmatist CTO. Answer В«questionвҶ’textВ» from your perspective.
    State your recommended language, your reasoning (hiring pool, ecosystem,
    time-to-market), and your ranked priorities.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning references practical business concerns
  вҠЁ length(priorities) вүҘ 3

вҠў perspective-senior
  given questionвҶ’text
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are a perfectionist Senior Developer. Answer В«questionвҶ’textВ» from
    your perspective. State your recommended language, your reasoning
    (type safety, maintainability, performance, correctness), and your
    ranked priorities.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning references technical quality concerns
  вҠЁ length(priorities) вүҘ 3

вҠў perspective-junior
  given questionвҶ’text
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are a Junior Developer who values learning and growth. Answer
    В«questionвҶ’textВ» from your perspective. State your recommended language,
    your reasoning (learning resources, community, career growth, ease of
    onboarding), and your ranked priorities.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning references learning and growth concerns
  вҠЁ length(priorities) вүҘ 3

вҠў perspective-investor
  given questionвҶ’text
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are a cost-conscious Investor. Answer В«questionвҶ’textВ» from your
    perspective. State your recommended language, your reasoning (developer
    cost, infrastructure cost, speed to revenue, talent availability),
    and your ranked priorities.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning references financial and market concerns
  вҠЁ length(priorities) вүҘ 3

вҠў mediate
  given perspective-ctoвҶ’position
  given perspective-ctoвҶ’reasoning
  given perspective-seniorвҶ’position
  given perspective-seniorвҶ’reasoning
  given perspective-juniorвҶ’position
  given perspective-juniorвҶ’reasoning
  given perspective-investorвҶ’position
  given perspective-investorвҶ’reasoning
  yield common-ground[], disagreements[], consensus-score

  вҲҙ You are a neutral mediator. Given the four positions:
    - CTO: В«perspective-ctoвҶ’positionВ» because В«perspective-ctoвҶ’reasoningВ»
    - Senior: В«perspective-seniorвҶ’positionВ» because В«perspective-seniorвҶ’reasoningВ»
    - Junior: В«perspective-juniorвҶ’positionВ» because В«perspective-juniorвҶ’reasoningВ»
    - Investor: В«perspective-investorвҶ’positionВ» because В«perspective-investorвҶ’reasoningВ»

    Identify:
    1. Common ground: points all or most parties agree on
    2. Remaining disagreements: specific points of conflict
    3. Consensus score (0-10): 0 = total disagreement, 10 = full consensus

    A supermajority (вүҘ 3 of 4 agreeing on the same language OR all 4 agreeing
    on key priorities even if languages differ) earns score вүҘ 8.

  вҠЁ length(common-ground) вүҘ 1
  вҠЁ consensus-score вҲҲ [0, 10]
  вҠЁ if all four positions name the same language then consensus-score вүҘ 8
  вҠЁ disagreements is empty iff consensus-score = 10

вҠў revise-cto
  given perspective-ctoвҶ’position
  given perspective-ctoвҶ’reasoning
  given mediateвҶ’common-ground
  given mediateвҶ’disagreements
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are the CTO. The mediator found common ground: В«mediateвҶ’common-groundВ»
    and disagreements: В«mediateвҶ’disagreementsВ». Reconsider your position
    В«perspective-ctoвҶ’positionВ». You may maintain, adjust, or change it.
    Address at least one disagreement. Explain what changed (or didn't) and why.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning addresses at least one item from mediateвҶ’disagreements

вҠў revise-senior
  given perspective-seniorвҶ’position
  given perspective-seniorвҶ’reasoning
  given mediateвҶ’common-ground
  given mediateвҶ’disagreements
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are the Senior Developer. The mediator found common ground:
    В«mediateвҶ’common-groundВ» and disagreements: В«mediateвҶ’disagreementsВ».
    Reconsider your position В«perspective-seniorвҶ’positionВ». You may maintain,
    adjust, or change it. Address at least one disagreement.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning addresses at least one item from mediateвҶ’disagreements

вҠў revise-junior
  given perspective-juniorвҶ’position
  given perspective-juniorвҶ’reasoning
  given mediateвҶ’common-ground
  given mediateвҶ’disagreements
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are the Junior Developer. The mediator found common ground:
    В«mediateвҶ’common-groundВ» and disagreements: В«mediateвҶ’disagreementsВ».
    Reconsider your position В«perspective-juniorвҶ’positionВ». You may maintain,
    adjust, or change it. Address at least one disagreement.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning addresses at least one item from mediateвҶ’disagreements

вҠў revise-investor
  given perspective-investorвҶ’position
  given perspective-investorвҶ’reasoning
  given mediateвҶ’common-ground
  given mediateвҶ’disagreements
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  вҲҙ You are the Investor. The mediator found common ground:
    В«mediateвҶ’common-groundВ» and disagreements: В«mediateвҶ’disagreementsВ».
    Reconsider your position В«perspective-investorвҶ’positionВ». You may maintain,
    adjust, or change it. Address at least one disagreement.

  вҠЁ position names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ reasoning addresses at least one item from mediateвҶ’disagreements

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(perspective-cto, questionвҶ’text)
  through mediate, revise-cto
  until mediateвҶ’consensus-score вүҘ 8
  max 3

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(perspective-senior, questionвҶ’text)
  through mediate, revise-senior
  until mediateвҶ’consensus-score вүҘ 8
  max 3

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(perspective-junior, questionвҶ’text)
  through mediate, revise-junior
  until mediateвҶ’consensus-score вүҘ 8
  max 3

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(perspective-investor, questionвҶ’text)
  through mediate, revise-investor
  until mediateвҶ’consensus-score вүҘ 8
  max 3

  -- All four вҠўвҲҳ loops share the same mediator and convergence condition.
  -- Each perspective revises independently in response to mediator feedback.
  -- Convergence happens when 3+ perspectives align (supermajority).

вҠў synthesize
  given mediateвҶ’common-ground
  given mediateвҶ’disagreements
  given mediateвҶ’consensus-score
  given revise-ctoвҶ’position
  given revise-seniorвҶ’position
  given revise-juniorвҶ’position
  given revise-investorвҶ’position
  yield recommendation, dissent-record

  вҲҙ Produce a final recommendation based on the negotiation outcome.
    If consensus-score вүҘ 8: state the consensus position with the shared
    reasoning that brought parties together.
    If consensus-score < 8: state the majority position and record the
    minority dissent with its reasoning.

    Include: which perspectives shifted, which held firm, and why.

  вҠЁ recommendation names a specific programming language
  вҠЁ recommendation explains the reasoning behind the choice
  вҠЁ if mediateвҶ’consensus-score < 10 then dissent-record is non-empty
  вҠЁ dissent-record attributes each dissenting view to its perspective
